            "answer_text": "Both \u201cindeed\u201d and \u201cinstead\u201d are grammatically correct. The meaning is very different. With \u201cindeed\u201d the statement is an affirmation that Jesus came and was the Messiah. With \u201cinstead\u201d it means that Jesus came but was not the Messiah. ",
