            },
            "answer_text": "\u2018Indeed\u2019 does not mean \u2018instead\u2019. Instead means \u2018in place of, something else\u2019. Indeed means \u2018truly, in truth\u2019. In order for your example to mean what you want it to mean, you must use \u2018indeed\u2019. If you say \u2018instead\u2019, you are saying that \u2018IN PLACE OF the messiah, Jesus came\u2019 and you would therefore be saying that Jesus was NOT \u2018the messiah\u2019, but that Jesus came INSTEAD - in the place of - the messiah. I don\u2019t think that is what you intend to say. ",
